HW2

Command line:
	Setting a variable:
	SET variable
	SET variable=string
	SET /A “variable=expression”
	SET “variable=”
	SET /P variable=[promptString]
	SET “
		Variable: A new or existing environment variable name e.g. _num
		String: A text string to assign to the variable
		Expression: Arithmetic expression
(http://ss64.com/nt/set.html)

Bash:
	Setting a variable:
	echo $SHELL (gives you name of current shell you are using)
	export VARIABLE=value
	export PATH=$HOME/bin/perl:$PATH (sets the path that the shell
	would be looking at when it has to execute any program)
(http://genepath.med.harvard.edu/mw/Bash:HOW_TO:_Set_an_environment_variable_in_the_bash_shell)

C:
	Getting a variable:
	The value of an environmental variable can be accessed with the getenv function. This is declared in the header file stdlib.h. 
	Function: char * getenv (const char *name)
(http://www.gnu.org/software/libc/manual/html_node/Environment-Access.html)
